headline.print_headline: Virginia Governor Will Veto Bid to Block Medicaid Expansion
headline.main: Virginia Governor Will Veto Bid to Block Medicaid Expansion

lead_paragraph: Virginia Governor Terry McAuliffe said Friday he will veto a Medicaid amendment to the state budget advanced by a Republican-dominated legislature that could prevent him from expanding access to the program through executive action.
